<h1>The Software Life-Cycle Models</h1>


<font color=red>
<h2>Waterfall Model</h2>
</font>
<h3>
<img src="s31.gif" height=750><br>Waterfall model<p>


(1) The feedback loops permits modifications to be made to
design documents, the software project management plan, and even
the specification document, if necessary.
<p>
(2) No phase is complete until the documentation for that phase
has been completed and the products of that phase has been
approved by the SQA group.
<p>
(3) Once the client has accepted the product, any changes constitute
maintenance.
<p>
(4) Inherent in every phase is testing.
<p>
<font color=red>Software configuration</font> is the entire set of documents,
including specification document, design document, code, user
manual, operations manual, etc.
</h3>
